&lt;/xsl:template&gt;           </codeblock>
                    <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/topics/ai-positron-code-development.dita" xtrc="p:15;192:24">This template processes the entire book structure in a single, nested
                        template using &lt;xsl:for-each&gt; for chapters and &lt;xsl:apply-templates&gt;
                        for sections. While this works, it can become difficult to maintain, extend,
                        or debug as the complexity of the XML structure grows.</p>
                    <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/topics/ai-positron-code-development.dita" xtrc="p:16;196:24">Use the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/topics/ai-positron-code-development.dita" xtrc="b:19;196:35">Suggest Refactoring</b> action and the AI will suggest to break it
                        into smaller templates:</p>
                    <codeblock id="codeblock_a15_hhf_bgc" outputclass="language-xml" xml:space="preserve" class="+ topic/pre pr-d/codeblock " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/topics/ai-positron-code-development.dita" xtrc="codeblock:10;198:86">&lt;xsl:template match="book"&gt;
